1 d. Applying cosmetic preparations, antiseptics, powders, oils, clays, or lotions to
2 scalp, face, neck, or upper part of the body.
3 4. "Restricted barber" means a licensee, limited in practice to specific areas in which
4 competence has been demonstrated, and allowed to work in a licensed host shop.
5 5. "Retired barber" means a licensee who meets the requirements of section 9 of this
6 Act.
7 6. "Temporary barber" means an eligible licensee who is permitted to practice under the
8 supervision of a licensed barber until results are available from the next scheduled
9 examination.
10 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 43-04-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
11 amended and reenacted as follows:
12 43-04-04. Board of barber examiners - Appointment - Term of office - Qualifications.
13 1. The board of barber examiners must consist of at least three members, each of whom
14 must be appointed by the governor for a term of three years.
15 2. Members are subject to the following requirements:
16 a. The terms of office of the members must be so arranged that one term expires on
17 the thirty-first day of December of each year.;
18 b. Each appointment must be made from a list of five names submitted to the
19 governor by the state barber association,; and each
20 c. Each member must be a registered barber who has followed the occupation of
21 barber in this state for at least five years prior tobefore that member's
22 appointment.
23 3. Two additional members, who shall serve as nonvoting ex officio members and are no t
24 required to be licensed barbers, may be appointed by the board for tasks including:
25 a. New and annual shop inspections;
26 b. Legal advice; and
27 c. Office duties.
