18 SECTION 7. A new section to chapter 43-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
19 and enacted as follows:
20 Restricted barber license - Requirements .
21 1. An individual may apply for a restricted barber license if the applicant:
22 a. Has not been disciplined relating to the practice of barbering in the previous five
23 years;
24 b. Passes a written examination of the laws and rules governing practice in the
25 state, as established by the board; and
26 c. Has a background in barbering as demonstrated by:
27 (1) Successfully completing a restricted barber course, as established by the
28 board, at a licensed barbering school or a barbering program within the
29 public school system; or
30 (2) Holding, within the previous five years, an active and valid license to
31 practice barbering in another state or country.
