1 2. A licensed restricted barber shall work in a licensed host shop and may not own or
2 operate a shop.
3 3. An individual may practice barbering while awaiting results of the examination under
4 this section, if the individual is under the supervision of a licensed barber in a licensed
5 barbershop, subject to the following:
6 a. An individual who fails the examination on the individual's first attempt may
7 continue practicing under the supervision of a licensed barber in a licensed
8 barbershop, provided the individual applies for the next examination;
9 b. The individual may continue to practice under the licensed barber until the
10 individual receives the results of the second examination; and
11 c. An individual may not continue to practice under this subsection if the individual
12 fails to pass the examination on the second attempt.
13 SECTION 8. A new section to chapter 43-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
14 and enacted as follows:
15 Temporary barber license - Requirements .
16 1. An individual who has met the requirements in subsection 2 of section 43 - 04 - 32 may
17 apply for and be issued a temporary barber license, upon payment of the required fee.
18 2. A license under this section:
19 a. Is valid for a maximum of three months;
20 b. Must begin from the verified date of graduation or completion of training; and
21 c. May be exercised only under the supervision of a licensed barber until results are
22 available from the next scheduled examination.
23 3. If the temporary license holder fails the examination, the temporary license holder may
24 apply for an extension of the individual's license under this chapter, pay the fee, and
25 register for the next scheduled examination.
26 SECTION 9. A new section to chapter 43-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
27 and enacted as follows:
28 Retired barber license - Requirements .
29 1. An individual may apply for a retired barber license and practice in a limited capacity if
30 the applicant is:
